.TH "find_volume" 9 "find_volume" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
find_volume \- find volume supported HW port by HW port number
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct uniphier_aio_sub *" find_volume
.BI "(struct uniphier_aio_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "int oport_hw "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
the AIO chip pointer
.IP "oport_hw" 12
HW port number, one of AUD_HW_XXXX
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Find AIO device from device list by HW port number. Volume feature is
available only in Output and PCM ports, this limitation comes from HW
specifications.
.SH "RETURN"
The pointer of AIO substream if successful, otherwise NULL on error.
